comment: T1: 2 mL. Ink shows a lot of contaminants/particulates, maybe cured bits from previous prints -> was not strained. Still curing. Discs with medium overcuring at bottom rim and some general defects. Moreover, 2/3 discs show missing part on one side stemming from erroneous projection (already reported by MF that this particular STL makes trouble). 2/3 okay as samples because third disc damaged upon detachment from printhead. Transferred to 2 mL tube with 1 mL DPBS for storage until measurement.

next steps: Change to small printhead. Recalibrate Z. Print again.
